Upheaval and Earthquake I figured in 63 seconds they would do 3195 damage, or 50dps per mob.  They also would have expended 3052 mana doing so.<br><br>Mages:<br><br>Scintilation 607 damage, 6.5 sec refresh, 3 second cast time, 361 mana<br>Flame Arc 181 damage, 7 sec refresh, 5.3 second cast time, 199 mana<br><br>Assuming the mage opens with Scintilation, and then rotates back and forth between Flame Arc and Scintilation I figured that the Mage would do 3940 damage in 64 seconds, or 61dps per mob.  The mage would expend 2800 mana doing so.<br><br><br>Few notes on all this:<br><br>Clerics efficiency will continue to go down until Unspoken Word pops again 2 minutes after it was first cast.<br><br>I used a standard 2.5 seconds spell gem refresh when calculating the mages damage output.  This could probably be decreased slightly by using a right click refresh item.  This would not have any effect on the cleric however since they must wait for their spells to refresh.<br><br>Cleric Unspoken Word is a level 59 Kunark Drop spell.  I don't know enough to know how rare it is, but if the cleric is either not 59, or has not aquired this spell, the damage output decreases significantly over the period of a minute.  Both Mage spells are purchased and usable by 51.  While the max damage won't be reached for a bit after that, they will pretty much meet the above expectations from 51 on.<br><br>One other thought that I had was that shorter casting time leads to less interrupts.  The Mage has the obvious advantage here.<br><br><br>My conclusion is that the mage, while working with less spells, has the far superior damage power and mana efficiency.  Obviously there is something to be said for having a extra cleric around, but if you are looking for damage, pick a mage over a cleric, but pick a wizard over both <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :smokin --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smokin.gif ALT=":smokin"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br><br><br>EDIT:  Added comment about short cast times.<br> <p><p style="MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0px; MARGIN-TOP: 0px"> </p><p style="MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0px; MARGIN-TOP: 0px" align="center"><font face="Tahoma"><font size="1"><font color="#ffffff"><img border="0" src="http://www.strengthofages.com/images/flamingxien.gif" width="71" height="49"> </font></font></font></p><p style="margin-right: 0; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 15px" align="center"><font face="Tahoma"><u><sup><sup><sup><font size="2" color="#00CCFF">59th</font><a href="http://www.graffe.com"><font size="2" color="#00CCFF"><b>Evoker</b></font></a><font size="2" color="#00CCFF">of <b>Solusek Ro</b></font></sup></sup></sup></u></font></p><p style="MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0px; MARGIN-TOP: 0px" align="center"><font size="1" face="Tahoma" color="#FFFFFF"><img border="0" src="http://www.strengthofages.com/images/woodleavestorakk.gif" width="183" height="29"> </font></p><p style="margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px" align="center"><u><sup><sup><font face="Tahoma" color="#006600" size="2">52nd<b> Suicidal</b> <b>Pathfinder</b> of <b>Tunare</b></font></sup></sup></u></p><p style="MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0px; MARGIN-TOP: 0px" align="center"><u><b><font face="Tahoma" color="#800000" size="2">Co-Leader</font></b><font color="#800000" size="2"></font><font face="Tahoma" color="#800000" size="1">of</font><font color="#800000" size="2"></font><b><i><a href="http://www.strengthofages.com"><font face="Tahoma" color="#800000" size="2">ArcaneStrength</font></a></i></b></u></p><p style="MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0px; MARGIN-TOP: 0px" align="center"><b><i><a href="http://pub42.ezboard.com/bayonaero"><font face="Tahoma" color="#800000" size="2">AyonaeRo Server</font></a><font face="Tahoma" size="1" color="#000000">  </font><font color="#FFFFFF">  </font></i></b></p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/usunsear.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sunsear</A> at: 1/17/02 5:15:40 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td